opengamma  derivatives software  balance sheet  margin our work our leadership news blog contact developers strata documentation forums github the heart of the derivatives market opengamma is the financial technology company at the heart of the derivatives market delivering unique analytics that marry buyside needs with sellside constraints transparency that builds confidence we provide the data and analytics you need to fully understand and optimise your derivative counterparty relationships the complete picture new regulatory capital constraints are redefining provider and user relationships we help buy and sellside participants appreciate how this impacts pricing working to build longer more sustainable relationships the opengamma difference our independent services provide an objective view of the allin costs for derivatives users helping the sellside minimise their balance sheet usage and providing the buyside with the information they need to make smarter counterparty decisions understand explore the pricing execution and clearing models that underpin the commercial relationships between market participants view wallet allocation and cost of trading understand the roa profile of your book you can also drill into your internal processes to improve efficiency compare line up the major clearing brokers and execution providers to compare the service you receive see how different commercial terms affect your spend see strategy level margin and capital usage breakdown analyse the full cost of different asset classes eg cleared vs uncleared tca optimise optimise your approach by using hard data to direct your business between counterparties allocate your book between counterparties to optimise your spend simulate different products  counterparties based on the estimated cost of trading   why now it’s a new world order  and that requires a fresh approach with the pressure on banks’ business lines relationships and pricing it’s vital for all participants to possess the knowledge to make the sharpest possible decisions that’s also why it’s never been more important to engage directly with counterparties after all in a complex regulatory environment dialogue and knowledge go handinhand to ensure that all sides of the trade benefit from a fair outcome     our work our recent engagements have included the following regulatory solutions otc clearing house margin models doddfrank act emir major rates and credit ccp margin models simm impact assessment of cleared vs uncleared clearing impact analysis and training for buy­side firms bilateral margining margin model bcbsiosco simm model licensed by isda model validation assistance impact analysis for cleared vs uncleared otc pricing and valuation bcbsiosco standardised valuation models bilateral derivatives valuation solutions for pension funds for swaps swaptions inflation swaps regulatory capital doddfrank act emir cem current exposure method for counterparty credit risk sa­ccr standardised counterparty credit risk frtb sba model implementation   our leadership peter rippon chief executive officer read bio maxime jeanniard du dot chief operating officer read bio jonathan senior chief technology officer read bio joe midmore head of sales read bio marc henrard head of quantitative research read bio   recent blogs insights tips and industry commentary from the team behind the world’s first productiongrade open source risk management platform  jun  elephant in the swap trading room exposing dealer trading costs for cleared and uncleared swaps by marc henrard read  feb  strata and multicurve interpolation and risk by marc henrard read  nov  strata and multicurve curve calibration and bucketed pv by marc henrard read  oct  csa changes do you really understand the impact by maxime jeanniard read  oct  gain visibility to verify your initial margin requirement by ken wong read     contact get in touch to find out more about opengammaemail infoopengammacom     location london albert house6 old st